predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Starlyng was born in 1460, in Dedham, Essex, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Anne. He died before 23 September 1504, in Suffolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1460–Bef 23 September 1504":"1460–enne 23. septembrit 1504","1476–Female":"1476–Surnud","1465–1504":"1465–1504","1485–1538":"1485–1538","1498–1541":"1498–1541","1500–1537":"1500–1537","1460–1504":"1460–1504","1500":"1500","Bef 23 September 1504":"enne 23. septembrit 1504","1498":"1498","1465":"1465","1476":"1476","1541":"1541","1485":"1485","1460":"1460","about 1485":"umbes 1485","1538":"1538","1537":"1537","1504":"1504","Dedham, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Dedham, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dedham, Essex, England":"Dedham, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1460–Bef 23 September 1504":"1460–ennen vuotta 23. syyskuuta 1504","1476–Female":"1476–Kuollut","1465–1504":"1465–1504","1485–1538":"1485–1538","1498–1541":"1498–1541","1500–1537":"1500–1537","1460–1504":"1460–1504","1500":"1500","Bef 23 September 1504":"ennen vuotta 23. syyskuuta 1504","1498":"1498","1465":"1465","1476":"1476","1541":"1541","1485":"1485","1460":"1460","about 1485":"noin 1485","1538":"1538","1537":"1537","1504":"1504","Dedham, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Dedham, Essex, Englanti,